      "id": "overview",
      "title": "## Overview",
      "content": "This plan outlines the creation of a real-time, multi-user coding competition web application called \"Decode the Crime\". It will feature user lobbies, an admin panel for game management, distinct hacker and detective roles, server-side game logic, integrated coding task judging via Judge0 API, a live leaderboard, an accusation system, moderator controls, and anti-cheat measures, all within an immersive, cyber-themed UI."
    },
    {
      "id": "key-features",
      "title": "## Key features",
      "content": "- **User Lobby**: Allows users to join and wait for a game to start.\n- **Admin Panel**: Enables administrators to create rooms, set participant limits, assign roles, and manage puzzles/tasks.\n- **Role Assignment**: Assigns users to 'hacker' or 'detective' roles.\n- **Coding Task Execution**: Runs hacker code tasks and detective puzzles, judged by the Judge0 API.\n- **Live Leaderboard**: Displays real-time scores and rankings of participants.\n- **Accusation System**: Allows detectives to make accusations.\n- **Moderator Controls**: Provides moderators with tools to start, pause, hint, disqualify, and export results.\n- **Anti-Cheat Measures**: Implements systems to detect and prevent cheating.\n- **Immersive UI**: Presents a cyber-themed visual experience.",
